= References

Reference objects create numbered references that appear in the document.

== Basic Reference

This is a reference {{ref code="REF1" content="Reference content here"}}.

== Reference with Link

This reference {{ref code="REF2" link="https://example.com"}} links to an external URL.

== Reference with Content

According to the study {{ref code="STUDY1" content="Smith et al. (2024). Important Research Study."}}, this is significant.

== Multiple References

First reference {{ref code="REF1" content="First reference content"}}.

Second reference {{ref code="REF2" content="Second reference content"}}.

Third reference {{ref code="REF3" link="https://example.com"}}.

== Reference Examples

The theory {{ref code="THEORY1" content="Einstein's Theory of Relativity"}} is well established.

Recent research {{ref code="RESEARCH1" link="https://example.com/research"}} shows new findings.

== Reference in Paragraphs

This paragraph contains a reference {{ref code="PARA1" content="Paragraph reference"}} to additional information.

== Reference Syntax

The reference object uses the format: `{{ref code="REF1" content="Reference text"}}` or `{{ref code="REF1" link="https://url"}}`

Where:
* `code` - Optional reference code (defaults to numbered code)
* `content` - Reference content text
* `link` - Alternative to content - creates a link reference
